{"questionId":"19756","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A factory produces engraved gold disks. The cost <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math> of the disks is directly proportional to the&nbsp;cube of the radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> of the disk.</p>\n<p>A disk with a radius of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo> </mo></math>cm costs <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>375</mn><mo> </mo></math>US dollars (USD).</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find an equation which links <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This sample question was produced by experienced DP mathematics senior examiners to aid teachers in preparing for external assessment in the new MAA course. There may be minor differences in formatting compared to formal exam papers.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>375</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>⇒</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>732</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>732</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>421</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>732</mn><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[3 marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19756","referenceCode":"EXN.1.SL.TZ0.2a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find an equation which links C and r.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}